3. A method of constructing a recombinant Yarrowia lipolytica strain overexpressing a keto acid transporter gene, comprising the steps of:
1) Constructing an integrative expression plasmid p0(hph) with hygromycin phosphotransferase as a selectable marker gene;
2) Constructing a recombinant integrative expression plasmid containing a keto acid transporter gene, wherein an open reading frame sequence of said keto acid transporter is chemically synthesized and subcloned into said integrative expression plasmid p0(hph);
3) Transforming said recombinant expression plasmid into Y. lipolytica; and
4) Screening for a positive transformant with said keto acid transporter gene integrated into its genomic DNA.

4. The method of claim 3, wherein said keto acid transporter gene is one or more than one genes selected from a group of nucleic acid sequences consisting of:
1) a nucleic acid sequence of Seq ID NO: 1;
2) a nucleic acid sequence of Seq ID NO: 3;
3) a nucleic acid sequence of Seq ID NO: 4; and
4) a nucleic acid sequence of Seq ID NO: 6.

5. A method of producing α-ketoglutarate using a recombinant Yarrowia lipolytica strain overexpressing a keto acid transporter, comprising the steps of:
1) Inoculating said recombinant Yarrowia lipolytica strain into a seed culture medium, and culturing at 28° C., 200 rpm for 16-18 hours;
2) Transferring cultured cells to a fermentation medium with an inoculum size of 5%-15%, and culturing at 28° C., 400 rpm for 144-168 hours with an aeration rate of 1.5 vvm.
